instrument.name: guitar family
instrument.description: Please help move wrongly credited relationships from this, most if not almost all should probably just be "guitar" with credit (guitars).

instrument.name: baroque guitar
instrument.description: Predecessor of the modern classical guitar, it had gut strings and even gut frets. First described in 1555, it surpassed the Renaissance lute's popularity.

instrument.name: harp guitar
instrument.description: The harp guitar is a guitar-based string instrument with any number of additional unstopped strings which can accommodate individual plucking.

instrument.name: tenor guitar
instrument.description: Slightly smaller, four-string version of the steel-string acoustic guitar.

instrument.name: flamenco guitar
instrument.description: Deriving from the classical guitar, it has many modifications and playing techniques to create a more percussive sound. Originally having wooden tuning pegs like lutes and violins, it has a thinner, lighter build with "golpeadores" or tapping-plates and less sustain than the classical guitar.

instrument.name: Portuguese guitar
instrument.description: Used in fado, it has twelve steel strings, strung in six courses.

instrument.name: classical guitar
instrument.description: Also known as Spanish guitar, it is used in classical, folk and other styles, the strings are nylon or gut.

instrument.name: Vietnamese guitar

instrument.name: guitar synthesizer
instrument.description: A guitar synthesizer is any one of a number of systems that allow a guitar player to play synthesizer sound.

instrument.name: archtop guitar
instrument.description: An archtop guitar is a steel-stringed acoustic or semi-acoustic guitar with a distinctive arched top, which is particularly popular with jazz players.

instrument.name: bass guitar
instrument.description: Bass member of the guitar family. For the electric variant use electric bass guitar for the acoustic one, use acoustic bass guitar.

instrument.name: electric bass guitar
instrument.description: Solid body 4-stringed electric bass guitar. The most common for "bass guitar" and "bass" credits in popular (rock) music.

instrument.name: steel-string acoustic guitar
instrument.description: Also know and "flat-top", it is a hollow-body acoustic guitar strung with steel strings.
